=head1 DESCRIPTION

Sets the number of I<concurrent processes> that transfer OData records
from your SAP instance. A concurrent process is query that retrieves a
batch of records as part of a flow run. Amazon AppFlow can run multiple
concurrent processes in parallel to transfer data faster.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> MaxParallelism => Int

The maximum number of processes that Amazon AppFlow runs at the same
time when it retrieves your data from your SAP application.



